metadata.name: steel conqueror
metadata.description:
3D COMPATIBLE

The pictures tell stories, clear and abstract. Past stories, which a closer look and feel reveal deep emotions and connections between objects and human life. 

It shows an enormous number of steel beams. Everything seems to be connected with each other,
each individual bearer seems to fulfill its own task. Although time has left its mark on all these steel giants in the form of rust, the framework still stands like a rock in the surf.

The interior of the steel mill is abandoned and seems to be dead. The spectator feels a soft knocking, as if the pipes wanted to scream loudly and be brought back to life.

This work of art represents a connection to the human body, life, and the flow of life.

The viewer is encouraged to connect with this true greatness, dynamics, and his own personality.
